# Privacy Policy for SnapMyShift

Effective Date: April 12, 2026

SnapMyShift helps users scan work schedules, create alarms, manage shifts, and export schedules to their calendar.

By using SnapMyShift, you agree to the collection and use of information as described in this Privacy Policy.

## Information We Access

SnapMyShift may request access to:

• Camera access, to capture schedule images for scanning
• Photos or selected media, if the user chooses images from their device
• Calendar access, if the user chooses to export shifts to their calendar
• Notifications, alarm permissions, foreground services, exact alarm permissions, and full-screen alarm permissions used for reminders and alarm functionality
• Limited device and app information such as device model, manufacturer, Android version, app version, and app-generated device identifiers

## How We Use Information

We use information to:

• Scan and process work schedule images
• Extract shift details using AI-powered processing
• Create alarms, reminders, notifications, and schedule alerts
• Export shifts to the user’s calendar
• Manage subscriptions, free trials, Founder access, and premium features
• Prevent abuse, fraud, unauthorized usage, and bypass attempts
• Enforce scan limits and subscription entitlements
• Improve app reliability, diagnostics, compatibility, and overall performance

## Image Processing

When users scan a schedule, images may be securely transmitted to backend services and AI processing providers in order to extract schedule information.

Images are processed only for schedule-reading functionality and are not sold to third parties.

## Device and Diagnostic Information

SnapMyShift may collect limited technical and diagnostic information including:

• Device model and manufacturer
• Android version and SDK version
• App version
• App-generated device identifiers
• Subscription and entitlement status
• Usage statistics related to scan limits and app functionality

This information is used strictly for app operation, abuse prevention, compatibility improvements, subscription enforcement, and reliability purposes.

## Subscriptions and Billing

Premium subscriptions, trials, and purchases are handled through Google Play Billing.

SnapMyShift does not directly collect or process credit card or payment information.

## Founder Access Terms

Founder Access is a limited one-time purchase available to the first 12 qualifying users.

Founder Access grants lifetime premium access under the current SnapMyShift premium subscription model and feature set available at the time of purchase.

SnapMyShift may introduce new optional features, services, integrations, enterprise functionality, cloud features, AI systems, premium processing systems, or separately licensed products in the future that may not be included as part of Founder Access.

Founder Access is non-transferable, tied to the original qualifying account, and may be revoked in cases of fraud, abuse, chargebacks, platform policy violations, unauthorized account sharing, or attempts to bypass usage protections or subscription systems.

## Data Storage

Some information may be stored locally on the user’s device, including:

• Saved schedules
• Alarm settings
• App preferences
• Locally cached shift information

Certain account-related and operational information may also be securely stored on backend systems used to operate app features, including:

• App-generated device identifiers
• Device model and Android version
• Subscription and entitlement status
• Usage limits and scan counts
• Alias/profile information
• App version and limited diagnostic information

## Data Sharing

We do not sell personal data.

We may share limited information with trusted service providers strictly required to operate app functionality, including:

• AI processing providers
• Cloud infrastructure providers
• Subscription and billing providers
• Analytics, diagnostics, or reliability providers

Information is shared only as necessary to operate the application and its services.

## Security

We take reasonable administrative, technical, and organizational measures to help protect information during transmission, processing, and storage.

However, no method of electronic transmission or storage is completely secure.

## Data Deletion

Users may remove app data by:

• Deleting schedules within the app
• Clearing app storage
• Uninstalling the application

Users may also contact us with deletion requests related to backend-stored account information.

## Children’s Privacy

SnapMyShift is not directed toward children under the age of 13.

## Changes to This Policy

This Privacy Policy may be updated periodically to reflect app updates, legal requirements, or operational changes. Continued use of SnapMyShift after changes become effective constitutes acceptance of the updated policy.

